The article provides information about the recent visit of National Security Advisor Jim Jones to Afghanistan and Pakistan. During his five-day trip, Jones met with leaders from both countries and assessed the progress of implementing the President's strategy in the region. In Afghanistan, he visited Kabul, Kandahar, Jalalabad, and Panjshir, and observed efforts related to security, development, and good governance. In Pakistan, Jones met with President Zardari, Prime Minister Gilani, Foreign Minister Qureshi, and Army Chief Kayani to discuss various issues, including development and security. He also visited the Swat Valley and other areas in the Northwest Frontier Province, where he commended the Pakistani Army and Border Forces for their successful security operations and acknowledged their sacrifices. The article emphasizes the commitment to a comprehensive and long-term relationship with Pakistan.